<br>
..While setting ups groups is a particular pain in the rear, with the low server population end game I'll guess that you'll have the cleric,chanter,warrior &lt;as they seem to be lacking&gt; names ingrained along with the who all *guild* should be sufficiant to get you names.<br>
<br>
..In seb, in my normal play times, i think i knew folks there better than some of my family. <br>
<br>
..Anyway when this was on test there was a big push to get /role enforced.<br>
<br>
While it does make your life alot more difficult it was something that was an option that they teted and asked feedback on.<br>
<br>
Why is the server population low ? Most folks gave up whatever they had on other servers to come here. The rule set is slightly harder than the other servers but not that bad. Most folk came tried it realised that they would have to do all of the stuff they had done before over again and said. nah I'll go back to my old server.<br>
<br>
..Whats left, folks that want to do the high end stuff but due to their old servers politics weren't able to, folks that did all that and decided to come here and just have fun and not worry about the end game. And some roleplayers.<br>
<br>
Thats my 2 cents not that they are worth anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 2:51:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=920.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This would be a huge ..</span><hr size=1> Oh, I know the problems.  I'm very aware of the low population on this server and the group-needs when you reach the higher levels.  I've played several classes to mid-level just to discover that I'm extremely dependent on groups.  (Which is one reason I liked my first bard character ... solo? sure.  Get a group? even easier.)<br>
<br>
But the forced /roleplay IS one of the many things that makes this server a lot different from any other.  I don't want to get /tells out of the blue &quot;Hi, elder brother bard.  Got some stuff a new singer can use?&quot;  or &quot;Hey, you're a bard, right?  Get your butt to Vox, we need you to sing resist buffs&quot;.  I can imagine it's even worse for clerics:  &quot;Hello Mr. Cleric, Rezz plz now thx ... &quot;<br>
<br>
Take the /roleplay away from the ruleset, and what you have is a server that's almost exactly like any other server<br>
<br>
the language barrier is not that big (easy to skill up while waiting for a group near a zone line)<br>
<br>
the alignment barrier can be overcome (everyone just choose neutral to make it easy)<br>
<br>
and city binding doesn't really matter when you have portals and translocates at the high-end game (who cares, only the unskilled use zergling tactics anyway).<br>
<br>
<br>
/roleplay forces the players on this server to find constant companions, trusted associates, and stable guilds.  Developing those relationships are a true test of social skills far different from &quot;/ooc Lord Room group looking for a healer, send tell&quot;.<br>
